    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 4d,e,f: Immunoelectron microscopic detection of immunogold labeling of Gγ7 (GNG7) by antisera showed localization to synaptic vesicles in cerebellar parallel fiber, climbing fiber and hippocampal Schaffer collateral presynaptic terminals.\n\nFigure 5c: similar observations are made in GABAergic presynaptic terminals in rat cerebellum. Synapses between basket cell axonal terminals and Purkinje somata were analyzed.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Deeply anesthesized rats were sacrificed by decapitation. The cerebellar cortex was immediately removed and cut into small cubes of about 8 mm3\"\n\nantibody:\n\"The following rabbit polyclonal antisera against G-protein subtypes were used: ... Gγ7 (AS 361; Leopoldt et al., 1997) ... All G-protein subtype-specific antisera were characterized for immunocytochemistry with respect to specificity and crossreactivity (Brunk et al., 1999; this paper).\"",
